different rate dependencies (9, 10, 36). Finally, we model spiral
wave dynamics in a two-dimensional (2D) sheet of human
ventricular tissue and study the dynamics of its rotation, the
ECG manifestation of the spiral wave, and membrane potential
recordings during spiral wave rotation. In conclusion, we
propose a new model for human ventricular tissue that is
feasible for
reentrant
sources of cardiac arrhythmias.

