Experimental data on IK1 current size are highly variable, as
previously discussed by Courtemanche et al. (8). We used the formu-
lation for IK1 used in the PB model but increased GK1 by a factor of
2 to account for the larger current densities found by Koumi et al. (33)
in the IK1-relevant voltage range (⫺90 mV to ⫺40 mV). This results
in a value for GK1 that is approximately ﬁve times larger than in the
CRN model, which agrees with data from Koumi et al. (33) showing
that IK1 is a factor of 5.6 higher in human ventricular than in atrial
myocytes.

