membrane where the Na⫹/Ca2⫹ exchanger is actually operating. Our
approach is similar to that used in the Noble et al. model with diadic
subspace (45), where INaCa was made dependent on diadic calcium
rather than bulk cytoplasmic calcium. Otherwise, during the AP
plateau phase the increase in bulk cytoplasmic calcium is not enough
to counteract the increase in voltage and INaCa current becomes
outward oriented during a long period of the plateau phase, which is
unrealistic (27).

