concentrations for different frequencies are in the range of
values measured by Pieske et al. (49). Figure 9C shows the
normalized systolic calcium level as a function of pacing
frequency. Assuming that generated force is linearly dependent
on systolic calcium, the calcium frequency staircase of our
model is similar to the force-frequency relationship obtained
experimentally for human myocardial cells by Pieske et al. (48,
49) and Schmidt et al. (57).

Different Cell Types

